article.description: Ty Groce had 15 points to lead six Eastern Michigan players in double figures as the Eagles routed Siena Heights 93-51 on Friday.
article.headline: Groce, James lead E. Michigan over Siena Heights 93-51
article.linkText: Groce, James lead E. Michigan over Siena Heights 93-51
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- Ty Groce had 15 points to lead six Eastern Michigan players in double figures as the Eagles routed Siena Heights 93-51 on Friday. Chris James added 14 points for the Eagles. Boubacar Toure had 13 points and 10 rebounds for his ninth career double-double, Yeikson Montero scored 11 and Noah Morgan added 11 points. Keith Jordan had 11 points for the Saints. Eastern Michigan (1-0) matches up against Goshen at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
